Written to `ADR-001-notification-architecture.md`.

**Summary of the recommendation:** Redis Streams, not Kafka. The deciding factors are team size (6 people, no infra engineer), existing Redis deployment, and throughput proportionality — Redis handles 100k+ ops/s vs our 500 req/s peak (5k at 10x). Kafka's operational cost and learning curve aren't justified when consumer-enforced exactly-once (idempotent keys in PostgreSQL) closes the gap at our volume. Kafka is flagged for revisit at 50k+ req/s or if event sourcing is adopted.
